        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><placeName>Zanesville</placeName> <date>May 27 53</date>. <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee> <sic>Revent</sic> Sir.</p>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p><persName role="author">W. Dryfus</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Zanesville</placeName>&#44; <date>May 27&#44; 1853</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>&#44; Reverend Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dearest friend&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Since I have written to you without re&#45;<lb/>ceiving any news. I again take the liberty to write to<lb/> you. I wrote to you about <persName>Mach</persName> whom I asked for<lb/> payment for the &#8220;Occident&#8221; &#40;&#36;6&#41;. He told me that he had re<lb/>ceived only 15 numbers and did not want to pay more<lb/> than &#36;4. I have also written to <persName>Mr. Mayers</persName> at <placeName>Frankf<add>&#63;</add><lb/> Kentucky</placeName>&#44; but have received no reply. You can write to<lb/> him yourself. He is in <placeName>Kentucky</placeName>&#8212;<persName>H. Mayers</persName>&#44; <placeName>Frankf<add>&#63;</add><lb/> Kentucky</placeName>. <persName>Mr. E. Mach</persName> does not want to pay more than<lb/> &#36;4. If you want to have it write to me immediately and<lb/> I shall send it at once. I know of nothing more to write at<lb/> present. I can get no subscribers for the &#8220;Occident&#8221; he<lb/> Please write to me at once.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">With best greetings&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Your friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">W. Dryfus</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
